The board of directors, Custodian and Allied Insurance Limited (General Business arm of the Custodian Group) has appointed Mr Edeki Isujeh as managing director/chief executive officer, following the approval of the National Insurance Commission. The company disclosed in a statement on Friday. It stated that Isujeh had over 30 yearsâ€™ experience in the insurance industry, having worked in different insurance companies in insurance operations, sales/business development and general management. At Custodian, he had at various times coordinated the marketing and technical operations of the company, the company said. It added that as a result of his commitment and hard work, he was appointed executive director of the company in 2016. He holds a Bachelor of Science degree in insurance from the University of Lagos and is a member of the Chartered Insurance Institute, London. Aside from various technical courses attended in and outside Nigeria, he had over the years attended management courses preparing him for leadership role. He is an alumnus of the Lagos Business School as well as the prestigious Wharton Business School, USA where he attended executive programmes. Isujeh was announced as the managing director of Custodian and Allied Insurance Limited following the retirement of the erstwhile Managing Director, Mr Toye Odunsi in December 2020. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com 